---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Communicate Accuracy and Reliability"
  description="Set expectations for how often the AI is right, when to double-check, and what might go wrongâ€”so users know when to trust and when to verify."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={112} label="Accuracy and reliability" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full">
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>When to Verify</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >Suggestions are usually accurate for common cases but can be wrong. Always review
            before applying, especially for important or unusual content. [Learn how we improve
            accuracy]</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >Users are told to review; no claim of perfection.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Confidence in Context</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >We're less confident in this answer because the source material is limited. Consider
            checking with a human expert before relying on it.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >When the system is uncertain, it says so and suggests verification.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-status-error-10 border border-status-error-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-200">
            <mds-icon name="mi/outline/error" class="text-status-error-05"></mds-icon>
            <mds-text typography="label"><b>Overstated Reliability (Problematic)</b></mds-text>
          </div>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >"Precise answers" or "Trust our AI" with no guidance on when to verify. No indication
            when the model is uncertain. Users assume they can rely on every output.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-status-error-06"
            >Overtrust leads to uncritical use; one failure can shatter confidence because
            expectations were wrong.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Tell users to review important outputs and that the AI can make mistakes; avoid implying it's
      always correct.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Use language like "precise", "accurate", or "trust our AI" without guidance on when to verify.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      When the system is uncertain or conditions are edge-case, say so and suggest human
      verification.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Present all outputs with the same implied certainty; hide or downplay uncertainty.
    </UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
